# Design Sprint (5-Day)

A time-boxed process for validating ideas through rapid prototyping and user testing.

## Config
flow = LR
spacing = 100

## Day 1: Map
- [d1] Define the long-term goal {icon:🎯} {fill:#89b4fa} {done}
  Where do we want to be in 2 years?
- [d1b] Map the challenge {icon:🗺} {fill:#89b4fa} {done}
  Diagram the user journey and mark the most critical point.
- [d1c] Pick the target {icon:📍} {fill:#89b4fa} {done}
  One moment on the map to focus on this week.

## Day 2: Sketch
- [d2] Lightning demos {icon:⚡} {fill:#cba6f7} {done}
  Review existing solutions and inspiring products.
- [d2b] 4-step sketch {icon:✏️} {fill:#cba6f7} {done}
  Notes → Ideas → Crazy 8s → Solution sketch.
- [d2c] Best idea selected {icon:⭐} {fill:#cba6f7}
  Each person's strongest concept.

## Day 3: Decide
- [d3] Vote and pick {icon:🗳} {fill:#a6e3a1} {wip}
  Sticky vote → heat map → supervote.
- [d3b] Storyboard {icon:📋} {fill:#a6e3a1} {wip}
  15-panel story of the user experience to prototype.

## Day 4: Prototype
- [d4] Build realistic prototype {icon:🔨} {fill:#f9e2af} {todo}
  Good enough to test — not production-ready.
- [d4b] Interview script {icon:📝} {fill:#f9e2af}
  5 questions around the prototype flow.

## Day 5: Test
- [d5a] 5 user interviews {icon:👁} {fill:#f38ba8} {todo}
  Watch 5 users interact with the prototype.
- [d5b] Pattern recognition {icon:🔍} {fill:#f38ba8}
  Look for recurring themes across interviews.
- [d5c] Decide: validate, pivot, or scrap {icon:🏁} {fill:#f38ba8}
  What did we learn? What next?

## Flow
d1 --> d1b --> d1c
d1c --> d2: day 2
d2 --> d2b --> d2c
d2c --> d3: day 3
d3 --> d3b
d3b --> d4: day 4
d4 --> d4b
d4b --> d5a: day 5
d5a --> d5b --> d5c

## Summary
Design Sprint: 5-day process to go from question to validated learning with real users.
